#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[135]
msgid "NEGOTIATION OF THE CONVENTION"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[137]
msgid ""
"An international team of users and survivors of psychiatry, led by Tina "
"Minkowitz, participated actively in the negotiations at the United Nations "
"(UN) in New York from the first session of the Ad Hoc Committee in August "
"2002 through the adoption of the completed text on December 13, 2006. The Ad "
"Hoc Committee was a unique process for all of us. We seized a historic "
"opportunity and accomplished something basic and fundamental that has "
"changed the human rights landscape for us and for all people with "
"disabilities. Many of us made lasting friendships with each other and with "
"other people with disabilities and allies, from around the world. Working "
"together closely, over the course of several years, in person at the UN and "
"by email discussions, we brought user/survivor issues into the heart of the "
"disability movement and found a rich common ground, especially on the issue "
"of legal capacity, which is the ultimate test of the guarantee of full and "
"equal enjoyment of human rights. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[140]
msgid "我们参与公约的起草和协商"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[142]
msgid ""
"一支由Tina Minkowitz领导的国际性的精神病学的使用者和幸存者队伍，积极参与了位"
"于纽约的联合国从2002年8月的AdHoc委员会的第一次会议，直至到2006年12月13日采用"
"完成的文本的全过程的协商当中。AdHoc委员会对于我们来说是一个独一无二的的过程。"
"我们抓住了一个历史性的机会并且实现了某种基本和重要的事情，这件事情已经改变我"
"们全部人和所有残疾人人的人权形势。我们许多人互相缔结了持续的友谊，也与其他残"
"疾人和全世界的同盟者们结下了友谊。一起紧密的工作，在过去几年的过程中，亲身在"
"联合国和通过电子邮件来讨论，我们把使用者/幸存者问题带到残障运动的中心，并且建"
"立了丰富的共同点，特别在法律能力的问题上，也是对充分和平等享有人权的保证的最"
"重要的考验。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[167]
msgid ""
"Users and survivors from the World Network of Users and Survivors of "
"Psychiatry (WNUSP), MindFreedom/Support Coalition International (MF/SCI) and "
"other organizations came to the UN from Canada, Denmark, Ghana, Guinea, "
"Hungary, Ireland, India, Japan, New Zealand, Nicaragua, Peru, Sweden, "
"Uganda, the United Kingdom, and the United States of America.  WNUSP members "
"served on New Zealand’s and Sweden’s government delegations.  We were an "
"impressive force.  WNUSP helped to create the International Disability "
"Caucus (IDC) and participated actively in its governance through our seat on "
"the steering committee.  The IDC had a principle of respecting the "
"leadership of disabled people’s organizations (DPOs), and respecting any "
"particular DPO on matters relating to its constituency. In addition, we "
"agreed that the Convention should “be equally relevant to all persons with "
"disabilities, irrespective of the type of disability or geographical "
"location”.  This helped to ensure solidarity."
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[202]
msgid ""
"WNUSP contributed several position papers of our own, including proposed "
"text for the treaty, much of which was accepted. When the IDC began working "
"together to present a unified position, we authored and/or coordinated the "
"work of the IDC on some important articles, including Article 12 on legal "
"capacity, Article 14 on liberty, Article 15 on torture, Article 17 on "
"integrity of the person, Article 22 on privacy, Article 23 on home and "
"family, Article 27 on employment, Article 29 on political participation, and "
"part of Article 25 on health. An important aspect of our work was building "
"alliances, building consensus, and learning to collaborate with other "
"disability rights activists. Finally the IDC spoke with one coherent and "
"powerful voice to promote a human rights agenda for all persons with "
"disabilities. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[204]
msgid ""
"WNUSP involvement started even before the first Ad Hoc Committee meeting, "
"when we learned of a meeting being held in Mexico City in June 2002 to bring "
"together experts to discuss the Convention. WNUSP requested and received an "
"invitation, and submitted a paper that set out the main tenets of our "
"advocacy as well as commenting on the draft text that the Mexican government "
"had prepared. The meeting successfully established our role in the community "
"of Non-Governmental Organizations (NGOs) and our advocacy was made part of a "
"paper agreed to by the NGOs at the meeting."
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[206]
msgid ""
"WNUSP贡献了我们自己的几项建议书，包括协议的提议文本，大部分被接纳了。当国际残"
"疾核心小组开始一起工作去提出一个统一的立场，在某些重要条款上，我们撰写和/或者"
"协调IDC的工作，包括关于法律能力的第12条，关于自由的第14条，关于酷刑的第15条，"
"关于病人的完整性的17条，关于隐私的第22条，关于住房和家庭的第23条，关于就业的"
"第27条，关于政治参与的第29条，和关于康复的第25条的部分文本。我们工作的的一项"
"重要方面是建立同盟，建立共识，和学习去与其他残疾权益积极分子进行合作。最终国"
"际残疾核心小组发出一致和强有力的声音，来促进所有残疾人的人权进程表。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[208]
msgid ""
"WNUSP的参与到公约当中，最早甚至要追朔到当我们得知2002年6月在墨西哥城举行的一"
"次会议，那次会议是聚集专家讨论公约，这是在参加第一次Ad Hoc委员会会议之前就已"
"经开始的了。WNUSP要求和接受了邀请，并且提交了一份文件，不但提出了我们倡导的基"
"本原则，也对墨西哥政府准备的起草文本表述意见。该会议成功地建立我们在非政府组"
"织共同体中的地位，并且我们的倡议在会议上被非政府组织接受成为文件的一部分。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[212]
msgid ""
"The first Ad Hoc Committee meeting established an agreement to continue the "
"process of “considering proposals for a Convention,” and the second (in June "
"2003) agreed to set up a working group to produce a draft text for "
"negotiation, drawing on proposals submitted by governments and civil society "
"(including WNUSP). Tina Minkowitz represented WNUSP as one of 12 NGOs that "
"participated in the working group, along with 27 governments and one "
"national human rights institution. In this group, which convened in January "
"2004, all participants had an equal voice and collaborated to produce the "
"resulting text. Users and survivors of psychiatry finally had a seat at the "
"table and spoke with a passion and clarity that was heard around the world. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[216]
msgid ""
"Then it was time for negotiation, when all governments and civil society "
"organizations (including those that had not participated in the working "
"group) had the opportunity first to improve the text, and then to settle on "
"a final version that everyone could live with. It was not an easy process, "
"and attempts were also made to weaken the text. However, the IDC’s approval "
"was sought and wanted, since we represented the constituency that is "
"supposed to benefit from the Convention. This was important for WNUSP in "
"securing recognition of equal legal capacity, liberty on an equal basis, "
"free and informed consent and right to respect for integrity of the person, "
"all without the limitations that had previously been inserted into documents "
"dealing with the rights of users and survivors of psychiatry. WNUSP and MF/"
"SCI participated in several side events during the Ad Hoc Committee meetings "
"primarily focusing on the importance of recognition of legal capacity on an "
"equal basis with others and of the freedom to make our own decisions. We "
"worked hard and lobbied hard, and had to listen to a lot of disrespectful "
"opinions. In the last stages of the process we had to deal with a betrayal "
"of our interests in a political process, when a footnote was inserted "
"limiting the meaning of legal capacity in Arabic, Chinese and Russian to "
"“capacity for rights” and not “capacity to act”. But we were able to turn "
"this around, with the help of our IDC allies and many governments who did "
"not accept the footnote, and removing the footnote was the victory that "
"capped our experience. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[240]
msgid ""
"WNUSP Co-chair Tina Minkowitz was one of the two IDC speakers that welcomed "
"the adoption of the Convention by the UN General Assembly on December 13, "
"and several other WNUSP and MF/SCI members were also present. On that day, "
"we all stood tall and proud of what we had accomplished, and Myra Kovary "
"summed it up by saying, “Let the revolution begin!”"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[242]
msgid ""
"The Convention was open for signing on March 30, 2007 and it was signed by "
"almost half of the UN member states on the opening day, indicating their "
"intent to ratify (become legally bound by the Convention). It is now the "
"task of the world community to bring the ideals that are laid out in the "
"Convention into reality. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[248]
msgid ""
"公约在2007年3月30日开放给成员国签署，在当日有大概一半联合国成员国签署了该公"
"约，表明他们在本国批准的意愿（成为法律上受公约制约）。现在使公约中的理想变成"
"现实也是国际社会的重要任务。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[251]
msgid "HOW TO USE THIS MANUAL"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[253]
msgid ""
"This manual is intended for users and survivors of psychiatry, and user/"
"survivor organizations, as an informational guide and reference for working "
"with the Convention. Users and survivors have the opportunity to work with "
"their government, through a national consultation process, on implementing "
"the Convention, and also incorporate the Convention into advocacy they are "
"doing (for instance, to get people out of institutions or stop forced "
"drugging or electroshock). The Convention is a rich document and people may "
"choose to focus on one or another area, depending on circumstances and "
"priorities. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[255]
msgid ""
"We have highlighted the aspects of the Convention that address the human "
"rights violations especially targeted against users and survivors of "
"psychiatry, in the areas of legal capacity, liberty and right to live in the "
"community, freedom from forced psychiatric interventions, our inclusion as "
"people with disabilities and participation in enforcement mechanisms. These "
"are the areas that we believe will make a difference in the lives of all "
"users and survivors of psychiatry, and without which other guarantees, such "
"as the right to work and the right to vote, are meaningless to us."
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[284]
msgid ""
"Users and survivors of psychiatry are urged to read this manual together "
"with the text of the Convention, and to apply it creatively to situations "
"they are facing. Besides guaranteeing specific rights, the Convention "
"requires equality and non-discrimination in the enjoyment of all human "
"rights and fundamental freedoms. If the Convention and this manual do not "
"address a particular situation, users and survivors can find the articles "
"that seem most relevant and make their best argument. Human rights lawyers "
"can help, but may also need to be educated by the user/survivor movement to "
"present our issues correctly. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[289]
msgid ""
"We face challenges in implementing the Convention, since there is as yet no "
"government that complies with its requirements in relation to users and "
"survivors of psychiatry. Many governments will contest the obligations in "
"the Convention and fight to keep their guardianship and mental health laws, "
"to continue psychiatric detention and violence, and promote a deficit-based "
"view of psychosocial disability requiring medical model “treatments”. They "
"will try to find loopholes or interpret it to make exceptions for the "
"obligations they would rather not comply with. However, we have had many "
"victories in the process of creating the Convention, and there are "
"encouraging signs that our message has been heard by some governments, and "
"that our allies in the disability and human rights communities will continue "
"to work with us at the international and national levels. The challenges we "
"face are not unique to our situation but are the same challenges faced by "
"any group of disenfranchised people claiming our human rights as recognized "
"in an international treaty. Our movement has matured a great deal through "
"the treaty process and will continue to meet the challenges to break through "
"to real change in the lives of users and survivors of psychiatry everywhere. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[293]
msgid "GUIDE TO THE TEXT"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[295]
msgid "1. HIGHLIGHTS OF THE CONVENTION"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[297]
msgid ""
"Q: What is the Disability Convention?A: Convention is another word for "
"treaty, a binding agreement between nations. The Convention on the Rights of "
"Persons with Disabilities (CRPD) is a multilateral treaty, a treaty among "
"many nations. It declares specific obligations of governments to respect and "
"enforce the human rights of persons with disabilities. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[299]
msgid "Q: Does the Convention cover users and survivors of psychiatry?"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[301]
msgid ""
"A: Article 1 of the CRPD states that the purpose of the Convention is to "
"protect and promote all human rights and fundamental freedoms of all persons "
"with disabilities. This article in its definition of persons with "
"disabilities includes those who have mental impairments. This formulation "
"clearly includes users and survivors of psychiatry."
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[303]
msgid ""
"A: The purpose of the Convention is to protect and promote all human rights "
"and fundamental freedoms by all persons with disabilities, including those "
"who have mental impairments. Users and survivors of psychiatry are covered "
"by this language."
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[306]
msgid "文章导读"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[2]/text:list-item[0]/text:p[0]
msgid "公约最重要的部分"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[307]
msgid "Q：残疾公约是什么？"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[308]
msgid ""
"A、公约是条约的另一个称谓，是国家之间的有约束力的协议。《残疾人权利公约》是一"
"个多边 的条约，一项多个国家之间条约。它宣告政府有特定的责任去尊重和加强残障人"
"士的人权。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[310]
msgid "Q：公约涵盖精神病学的使用者和幸存者吗？"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[312]
msgid ""
"A：《残疾人权利公约》的第一条声明公约的目的是保护和促进所有残疾人的所有人权和"
"基本自由。本条款关于残疾人的定义包括精障人士。这个表述清楚包括精神病学的使用"
"者和幸存者。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[313]
msgid "-"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[314]
msgid ""
"A：公约的目的是为了保护和促进所有残障人士，包括那些精障人士的所有人权和基本自"
"由。这个语言叙述涵盖了精神病学的使用者和幸存者。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[328]
msgid "Q: How does the Convention deal with the issue of legal capacity?"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[330]
msgid ""
"A: The concept of legal capacity has been used to deny personhood and to "
"disqualify users and survivors from managing our own lives. Art 12 of the "
"CRPD has dismantled these deprivations by conferring personhood to all "
"persons with disabilities and by recognizing that we have the legal capacity "
"to run our own lives. Also if we so desire, we can seek support to exercise "
"our legal capacity. Thus support is no longer inflicted upon us whether we "
"want it or not, rather it is assistance which has to be made available if we "
"wish to use it. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[334]
msgid ""
"A：法律能力这个概念曾经被用作否认人格和剥夺使用者和幸存者管理我们自己的生活的"
"资格。公约的第12条已经通过向所有残疾人赋予人格和通过承认我们拥有管理我们生活"
"的法律能力，来废除这些对残疾人权利的剥夺。同样如果我们要求，我们可以寻求支持"
"来行使我们的法律能力。这样，无论我们是否需要，支持就不再是强加于我们的，而是"
"当我们希望行使法律能力时的必须提供给我们的帮助。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[368]
msgid "Q: Does the Convention prohibit forced drugging and electroshock?"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[370]
msgid ""
"A: Article 17 grants to all persons with disabilities the right to respect "
"for their physical and mental integrity on an equal basis with others. It is "
"this right which protects persons who do not have disabilities from "
"unwelcome treatment, forcible confinement or any other unwelcome invasion of "
"their body and mind. Article 17, by its guarantee of equality and non "
"discrimination, also makes these available to us. This guarantee is further "
"strengthened by the fact that article 25 obliges health care professionals "
"to provide treatment only on the basis of free and informed consent. Free "
"and informed consent can only be given by the person concerned, and not by "
"family members, courts or others. (This follows from the guarantee of legal "
"capacity). In addition under article 15 the Convention protects the right to "
"freedom from torture and cruel, inhuman or degrading treatment or "
"punishment, which includes medical or scientific experimentation without "
"consent. The cumulative effect of these provisions is to oust forced "
"psychiatry. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[373]
msgid "Q：公约禁止强制性服药和电击治疗吗？"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[402]
msgid ""
"Q: Does the Convention allow forced institutionalization/ hospitalization? "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[404]
msgid ""
"A: Persons with disabilities have the right to liberty on an equal basis "
"with others, and deprivation of liberty cannot be justified on the basis of "
"disability. People with disabilities also have the right to live in the "
"community, and to choose where and with whom to live, on an equal basis with "
"others (and legal capacity ensures that each person can exercise this right "
"directly and not have a guardian or family member substitute their "
"decision). Forced institutionalization or hospitalization on the basis of "
"disability is therefore prohibited. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[444]
msgid ""
"Q: What does the Convention say about people with psychosocial disabilities "
"who are a danger to others?"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[448]
msgid "Q: How will the Convention be enforced?"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[450]
msgid ""
"A: An international monitoring committee will be set up to receive reports "
"from governments and make recommendations; the international committee can "
"also receive complaints from individuals whose rights have been violated, "
"but only if the government has ratified the Optional Protocol along with the "
"Convention. There will be a national focal point for implementation in the "
"government, and also a national monitoring mechanism with independent "
"powers. Along with other persons with disabilities, users and survivors of "
"psychiatry have the right to participate in government processes to "
"implement the Convention (e.g. law reform and policymaking)."
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[452]
msgid "问：公约关于对他人造成危险的社会心理残障人士有什么说法？"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[453]
msgid ""
"答：在与他人平等基础上的，侵犯他人权利的残疾人有权利受到警察和刑法系统的待"
"遇，包括合理便利。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[455]
msgid "问：公约将会如何被执行？"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[456]
msgid ""
"答：将会设立一个国际监察委员会，来接受政府报告和作出建议；只有在政府已经批准"
"附于公约的可选协议的情况下，该委员会也可以接受来自权利受到侵犯的个体的投诉。"
"在政府的执行公约中将会有国家焦点，并且也有一个国家独立力量的监察机制。和其他"
"残疾人一道，精神病学的使用者和幸存者有权利参与到政府执行公约的进程中来（例"
"如：法律改革和政策制定）。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[459]
msgid "2. GUIDE TO TERMINOLOGY, DEFINITIONS AND DESCRIPTIONS "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[461]
msgid ""
"During the negotiations, it was impossible for the parties to agree on a "
"definition of disability that included all persons with disabilities and "
"excluded no person with a disability. The Preamble of the Convention in "
"subparagraph (e) recognizes “that disability is an evolving concept.” "
"Article 1 of the Convention states that, “The purpose of the present "
"Convention is to promote, protect and ensure the full and equal enjoyment of "
"all human rights and fundamental freedoms by all persons with disabilities, "
"and to promote respect for their inherent dignity. Persons with disabilities "
"include those who have long-term physical, mental, intellectual or sensory "
"impairments which in interaction with various barriers may hinder their full "
"and effective participation in society on an equal basis with others.”"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[3]/text:list-item[0]/text:p[0]
msgid "术语、定义和描述的导读"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[468]
msgid ""
"During the course of the negotiations, WNUSP developed language to refer to "
"persons with psychiatric disabilities that moved away from the medical model "
"of individual pathology. We described ourselves as persons with psychosocial "
"disabilities. The word psychosocial refers to the interaction between "
"psychological and social/cultural components of our disability. The "
"psychological component refers to ways of thinking and processing our "
"experiences and our perception of the world around us. The social/cultural "
"component refers to societal and cultural limits for behavior that interact "
"with those psychological differences/madness as well as the stigma that the "
"society attaches to labeling us as disabled. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[487]
msgid ""
"However, in using the term psychosocial, we have no in intention of "
"associating ourselves with the psychosocial rehabilitation movement. The "
"term psychosocial disability is not yet understood in most countries of the "
"world, and therefore, at the end of the negotiations, we agreed to use the "
"more generally understood terminology of mental impairment in the text of "
"the Convention. Persons with mental impairments include users and survivors "
"of psychiatry who experience or have experienced experiencing madness and/or "
"mental health problems and/or are using or surviving, or have used or "
"survived psychiatry/mental health services, as well as those of us who are "
"perceived by others as having a mental disability/impairment. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[491]
msgid ""
"We prefer to use the term “psychosocial disability” and would like to "
"introduce it into the vocabulary rather than use the term “mental "
"impairment” when we are lobbying for implementation of the Convention. We "
"recognize that there may be difficulties in translating the word "
"“psychosocial” into languages other than English. We urge members of WNUSP "
"to confer with each other and use their best judgment in making the "
"translation. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[493]
msgid ""
"我们宁愿使用术语“社会心理残疾”，并且在我们为实施公约进行游说时愿意把它引入词"
"汇库，而不是使用术语“精神残障”。在把“社会心理”一词翻译成除英语以外的语言时，"
"我们承认可能存在困难。我们促使WNUSP成员相互对照和在做翻译时使用他们最佳的判"
"断。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[495]
msgid "3. THE PRINCIPLES OF THE CONVENTION"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[497]
msgid ""
"The general principles of the Convention are articulated in Article 3 as "
"follows:"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[499]
msgid ""
"(a) Respect for inherent dignity, individual autonomy including the freedom "
"to make one’s own choices, and independence of persons;"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[501]
msgid "(b) Non-discrimination;"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[503]
msgid "(c) Full and effective participation and inclusion in society;"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[505]
msgid ""
"(d) Respect for difference and acceptance of persons with disabilities as "
"part of human diversity and humanity;"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[507]
msgid "(e) Equality of opportunity;"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[509]
msgid "(f) Accessibility;"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[511]
msgid "(g) Equality between men and women;"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[513]
msgid ""
"(h) Respect for the evolving capacities of children with disabilities and "
"respect for the right of children with disabilities to preserve their "
"identities."
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[515]
msgid ""
"There are some important concepts in the preamble that do not reappear in "
"the binding articles."
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[4]/text:list-item[0]/text:p[0]
msgid "公约的原则"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[518]
msgid "公约的一般原则在以下的第三条清晰阐述："
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[521]
msgid "（b）非歧视；"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[524]
msgid "（e）机会的平等；"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[525]
msgid "（f）便利性；"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[526]
msgid "（g）男女之间的平等；"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[527]
msgid "（h）尊重演变中的残疾儿童的能力，和尊重残疾儿童的权利来保护他们的身份。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[529]
msgid "在序言中有一些重要的概念不会再在应履行的条款中出现。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[542]
msgid ""
"(e) recognizes that disability is an evolving concept and that disability "
"results from the interaction between persons with impairments and "
"attitudinal and environmental barriers that hinder their full participation "
"in society on an equal basis with others "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[544]
msgid "(i) recognizes the diversity of persons with disabilities"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[546]
msgid ""
"(j) specifically includes those persons with disabilities who require more "
"intensive support"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[548]
msgid ""
"(p) concerned about multiple forms of discrimination and specifically "
"mentions discrimination on the basis of indigenous origin"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[550]
msgid ""
"(t) highlights that the majority of persons with disabilities live in "
"poverty and recognizes the critical need to address the negative impact of "
"poverty on persons with disabilities."
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[552]
msgid ""
"The application of these principles will radically alter the lives of "
"persons with psychosocial disabilities. Some of the consequences will be:"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[554]
msgid ""
"- the abolition of mental health commitment laws, guardianship, and the "
"insanity defense"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[556]
msgid "- the creation of a wide range of healing support, and"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[558]
msgid "- the liberation of our people from institutions."
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[560]
msgid "序言："
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[562]
msgid "（i）承认残疾人的多元性"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[563]
msgid "（j）特定地包括那些需要更加深入细致的支持的残疾人 "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[564]
msgid "（p）关心多种形式的歧视和特定地提到基于固有来源的歧视"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[565]
msgid ""
"（t）突出强调大多数残疾人生活在贫困中，并且承认对于强调贫困对于残疾人的负面影"
"响的极重要的需要"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[567]
msgid "这些原则的应用将会彻底地改变社会心理残疾人士的生活。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[568]
msgid "将会有一些结果："
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[570]
msgid "- 精神健康收治法律、监护人制度以精神病防御的及废除"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[572]
msgid "- 我们残障人士从医疗等机构的释放 "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[573]
msgid ""
"4. SUMMARY OF THE PROVISIONS IN THE CONVENTION AND GUIDE TO IMPLEMENTATION"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[575]
msgid ""
"Article 1 sets out the purpose of the Convention, to guarantee equal "
"enjoyment of all human rights and fundamental freedoms to all people with "
"disabilities, and names certain groups of people with disabilities as being "
"included (people with long-term physical, mental, sensory and intellectual "
"impairments which in combination with various barriers may hinder "
"participation in society). "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[577]
msgid "Article 2 sets out definitions including definitions of "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[579]
msgid ""
"• “discrimination on the basis of disability” (a distinction on the basis of "
"disability that has the purpose or effect of limiting human rights or "
"fundamental freedoms, and discrimination includes the denial of reasonable "
"accommodation) "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[581]
msgid ""
"• “reasonable accommodation” (adjustments needed in a particular case to "
"ensure equal enjoyment and exercise of human rights and fundamental freedoms)"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[583]
msgid "Article 3 sets out principles of the Convention, including:    "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[584]
msgid "• Individual autonomy, including the freedom to make one’s own choices"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[585]
msgid "•   Respect for disability as part of human diversity"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[586]
msgid "• Non-discrimination "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[5]/text:list-item[0]/text:p[0]
msgid "公约条款摘要和执行指南"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[589]
msgid "第二条：阐述定义包括以下定义："
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[590]
msgid ""
"“基于残疾的歧视”（有限制人权和基本自由的目的或影响的基于残疾的区分，和包括对"
"合理便利的拒绝）"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[592]
msgid ""
"“合理便利”（对于确保平等享用和行使人权和基本自由，在特定的案例中需要的调整）"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[594]
msgid "第三条：阐述公约的原则，包括："
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[596]
msgid "个人自主权，包括自主做决定的自由"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[598]
msgid "对残疾尊重，作为人类多元化得一部分"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[600]
msgid "非歧视 "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[606]
msgid ""
"Article 4 guarantees all human rights and fundamental freedoms to people "
"with disabilities without discrimination, and requires governments to change "
"their laws and practices to comply with the Convention. An important "
"provision in Article 4 obligates governments to consult closely with "
"organizations of people with disabilities in implementing the convention and "
"in all issues relating to people with disabilities."
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[607]
msgctxt "office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[607]"
msgid "What needs to be done:"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[609]
msgid ""
"Article 4 can be used by itself or in conjunction with other articles of the "
"Convention to do away with laws, policies and practices that violate the "
"human rights of people with disabilities."
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[610]
msgid ""
"1) All discriminatory laws must be repealed. This includes guardianship or "
"incapacity laws, provisions disqualifying people from legal acts based on "
"disability (such as exercising the right to vote or to marry), and mental "
"health laws authorizing deprivation of liberty or psychiatric interventions "
"without the free and informed consent of the person concerned."
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[611]
msgid ""
"2) Discrimination against people with psychosocial disabilities must be "
"prohibited by law. Psychosocial disability must be included on an equal "
"basis with other types of disability in anti-discrimination legislation."
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[612]
msgid ""
"3) Governments must ensure that public officials and agencies do not "
"discriminate based on disability or otherwise violate the Convention. "
"Governments must also take measures to eliminate discrimination by "
"individuals, organizations or private enterprises. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[6]/text:list-item[0]/text:p[0]
msgid ""
"：没有歧视下保证残疾人的所有人权和基本自由，并要求政府修改它们的法律和做法来"
"遵从公约。第四条的一条重要条款要求政府有责任在执行公约和与残疾人相关的问题中"
"与残疾人组织紧密商议。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[619]
msgctxt "office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[619]"
msgid "需要做什么："
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[620]
msgid ""
"第四条可以单独应用，也可以与公约中的其他条款联合应用，来废除侵犯残疾人的人权"
"的法律、政策、和做法。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[621]
msgid ""
"1）所有歧视性法律必须废除。这包括监护人制度或者无行为能力法律，基于残疾的剥夺"
"残疾人进行法律行为的条款（譬如行使投票权和结婚权）、以及批准没有自由和当事人"
"知情同意下的对于自由的剥夺或者精神病学的干预。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[622]
msgid ""
"2）对于社会心理残疾人士的歧视必须受到法律禁止。社会心理残疾必须在与其他类型残"
"障平等的基础上包括在反歧视立法中。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[623]
msgid ""
"3）政府必须确保公共官员和机构不基于残疾歧视或以另外方式违反公约。政府也必须采"
"取措施消除来自个人、组织或私人企业的歧视。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[624]
msgid "4）强制性的和暴力式的干预构成歧视，必须被废除。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[625]
msgid ""
"5）精神病学的使用者和幸存者的组织有权利被在公约的执行和所有与我们相关的法律和"
"政策的事务中被咨询。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[626]
msgid "6）执行公约的保证并且为侵犯提供法律救济。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[628]
msgid ""
"Article 5 guarantees equal protection and equal benefit of the law and "
"prohibiting discrimination based on disability, and requires reasonable "
"accommodation to be provided. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[629]
msgctxt "office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[629]"
msgid "What needs to be done:"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[631]
msgid ""
"1) Prohibit all forms of discrimination and enforce anti-discrimination "
"laws. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[633]
msgid ""
"2) Identify what reasonable accommodation means for people with psychosocial "
"disabilities and ensure that such accommodation is provided. Situations "
"where reasonable accommodation may be needed include interactions with "
"government agencies (including police and penal law systems), education, "
"work, and exercise of legal capacity (supported decision-making). "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[635]
msgid ""
"Article 6 guarantees to women and girls with disabilities the equal "
"enjoyment of human rights and fundamental freedoms, and requires measures "
"for the advancement, development and empowerment of women. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[7]/text:list-item[0]/text:p[0]
msgid ""
"保证法律规定的平等保护和平等权益，并且禁止基于残疾的歧视，并要求提供合理便"
"利。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[637]
msgid "1）禁止所有形式的歧视和执行反歧视法律。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[638]
msgid ""
"2）确认何种合理便利对社会心理残疾人士的意义，并确保提供该种便利。需要合理便利"
"的情况包括与政府机构（包括警察和刑法制度）、教育、工作和行使法律能力等的互动"
"（支持性自主决策）。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[640]
msgid ""
"第六条 确保残疾妇女和残疾女孩平等享有人权和基本自由，并且要求采取措施，确保妇"
"女地位得到提高，得到充分发展，能力得到增强。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[667]
msgid ""
"1) Protect women and girls from discrimination based on gender, disability "
"or the interaction of gender and disability. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[669]
msgid ""
"2) Identify areas of multiple or intersecting discrimination affecting women "
"and girls who are users and survivors of psychiatry, and take appropriate "
"action. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[671]
msgid "For example:"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[673]
msgid ""
"Gender-based violence and discrimination is mutually reinforcing with "
"psychiatric violence, such as:"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[675]
msgid "• Psychiatric labeling of the experience of rape survivors"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[677]
msgid "• Institutions confining women and men together, facilitating rape"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[679]
msgid ""
"• Effect of electroshock and psychiatric drugs in destroying women’s ability "
"to resist oppression"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[681]
msgid ""
"• These violations are not limited to women, but are a defining part of "
"women’s experiences as survivors of psychiatry; obligations to prevent "
"violence (Article 16) and combat cultural stereotypes (Article 8), as well "
"as similar obligations under the Convention to Eliminate Discrimination "
"Against Women (CEDAW), should be addressed from a gender and disability "
"perspective to include such matters. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[683]
msgctxt "office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[683]"
msgid "需要做什么："
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[8]/text:list-item[0]/text:p[0]
msgid "保护妇女和女孩免于基于性别、残疾或性别和残疾的相互作用的歧视。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[8]/text:list-item[1]/text:p[0]
msgid ""
"确定影响身为精神病学的使用者和幸存者的妇女和女孩的、多重或交叉歧视的范围，并"
"采取合适行动。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[685]
msgid "例如："
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[686]
msgid "基于性别的暴力和歧视是与精神病学暴力相互加强的，譬如："
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[688]
msgid "强奸幸存者的经历的精神病学标签化"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[690]
msgid "机构把妇女和男人监禁在一起，促进强奸"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[692]
msgid "电击和精神科药物对破坏妇女抵抗压迫的能力的影响"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[694]
msgid ""
"这些侵犯不仅限于妇女，而是作为精神病学幸存者的妇女的经历的一个决定性的部分；"
"防止暴力（第16条）的责任和与文化的陈规旧习作斗争（第八条），和在《消除妇女歧"
"视公约》中的类似的责任，应该通过从包括类似事情的性别和残疾的角度来解决。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[697]
msgid ""
"Article 7 guarantees to children with disabilities the same rights as other "
"children, including the right to express themselves freely and have their "
"views taken into account on matters concerning them, and to have age- and "
"disability-appropriate support in exercising these rights."
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[699]
msgctxt "office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[699]"
msgid "What needs to be done:"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[701]
msgid ""
"1) Ensure that children are listened to and their wishes respected regarding "
"the use of mental health and other services. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[703]
msgid ""
"2) Children must not be subjected to electroshock, psychosurgery, or "
"neuroleptic drugs. Any other psychiatric interventions must include the "
"participation of the children with respect for their right to health care on "
"the basis of free and informed consent (see Article 25) in the context of "
"their evolving capacities as defined in Article 12 of the United Nations "
"Convention on the Rights of the Child. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[705]
msgid ""
"3) Provide children with appropriate support to understand matters "
"concerning them and to express their views."
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[9]/text:list-item[0]/text:p[0]
msgid ""
"保证残疾儿童拥有与其他儿童相同的权利，包括自由表达意见和在与他们相关的事情伤"
"考虑他们意见的权利，并且在行使这些的权利时拥有与年龄和残疾相适合的支持。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[10]/text:list-item[0]/text:p[0]
msgid ""
"儿童不能遭受电击、精神外科手术、或者抗精神病。任何其他精神病学的干预必须包括"
"儿童的参与，并尊重他们基于自由和知情同意（见第25条）的卫生保健的权利，这些内"
"容体现在《联合国儿童权利公约》第12条的所定义的他们演变中的能力的文本当中。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[10]/text:list-item[1]/text:p[0]
msgid "向儿童提供合适的理解关于他们的事物和表达他们观点的支持。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[733]
msgid ""
"Article 8 addresses awareness-raising and requires governments to foster "
"respect for the rights of people with disabilities and to combat prejudice "
"and harmful practices, at all levels of society including families and "
"communities. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[734]
msgctxt "office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[734]"
msgid "What needs to be done:"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[736]
msgid ""
"1) Promote language and concepts that are positive and non-judgmental about "
"states of mind and ways of expressing oneself. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[738]
msgid ""
"2) Assist communities to develop the capability to support and interact with "
"people in crisis."
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[740]
msgid ""
"3) Develop and teach non-violent and non-discriminatory methods of conflict "
"resolution. It is not acceptable to use psychiatric labeling, "
"institutionalization, or interventions, or legal incapacitation, to resolve "
"conflicts. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[11]/text:list-item[0]/text:p[0]
msgid ""
"提出提高意识和要求政府形成对残疾人的权利的尊重，并且在包括家庭和社区的社会的"
"各个层面与偏见和有害的做法作斗争，"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[744]
msgctxt "office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[744]"
msgid "需要做什么："
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[12]/text:list-item[0]/text:p[0]
msgid "促进对于思想状态和表达方式的积极和非判断性的语言和概念。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[12]/text:list-item[1]/text:p[0]
msgid "协助社区去发展支持以及与危机中的人士互动的能力。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[12]/text:list-item[2]/text:p[0]
msgid ""
"发展和教育对于冲突解决的非暴力和非歧视性的方法。使用精神病标签化、制度化，或"
"者干预、或者法律化的使丧失能力等解决冲突的方法是不被接受的。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[768]
msgid ""
"Article 9 requires states to take measures to ensure access by persons with "
"disabilities on an equal basis with others to the physical environment, "
"transportation, information and communications, and other facilities and "
"services provided to the general public. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[770]
msgctxt "office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[770]"
msgid "What needs to be done:"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[772]
msgid ""
"Ensure that the access needs of people with psychosocial disabilities are "
"identified and addressed, in consultation with user/survivor organizations."
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[13]/text:list-item[0]/text:p[0]
msgid ""
"要求国家采取措施确保残疾人士在与其他人平等的基础上，无障碍地获得物质环境、使"
"用交通工具、利用信息和通讯，和其他向普通公众提供的设施和服务。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[777]
msgctxt "office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[777]"
msgid "需要做什么："
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[779]
msgid ""
"在与使用者和幸存者组织的商议中，确保社会心理残疾人士的无障碍需求被确认和强"
"调。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[781]
msgid ""
"Article 10 reaffirms the right to life of all human beings and obligates "
"governments to ensure its effective enjoyment by people with disabilities on "
"an equal basis with others."
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[782]
msgid ""
"The right to life (Article 10) does not override the right to liberty "
"(Article 14) when it comes to issues of suicidality. The right to life "
"cannot be superseded by the right to liberty. Both rights must be respected. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[784]
msgctxt "office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[784]"
msgid "What needs to be done:"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[786]
msgid ""
"1) Prosecute murders of people with disabilities, and ensure the means of "
"survival for people with disabilities on an equal basis with others."
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[14]/text:list-item[0]/text:p[0]
msgid ""
"Suicide and assisted suicide are controversial in the disability community. "
"Suicide may be a valid personal choice, but it can also be a response to "
"preventable conditions of deprivation, violence and discrimination. Neither "
"criminal sanctions nor coercive psychiatry is an appropriate response to "
"suicidal attempts or wishes. People with experience of suicidality should be "
"considered experts on this issue when developing law and policy."
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[15]/text:list-item[0]/text:p[0]
msgid ""
"重申所有人类的生命权，和使政府有责任确保让残疾人在与其他人平等的基础上有效地"
"享有它。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[789]
msgid ""
"当提到自杀问题时，生命权（第十条）并不优先于自由权。生命权不能被自由权所取"
"代。两项权利都必须受到尊重。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[791]
msgctxt "office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[791]"
msgid "需要做什么："
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[16]/text:list-item[0]/text:p[0]
msgid ""
"对谋杀残疾人进行控告，并且确保残疾人在与其他人平等的基础上拥有生存的方式。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[796]
msgid ""
"Article 11 requires governments to respect international human rights and "
"humanitarian law in situations of armed conflict, humanitarian emergencies "
"and natural disasters, and take measures to ensure the safety of people with "
"disabilities in these circumstances."
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[798]
msgctxt "office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[798]"
msgid "What needs to be done:"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[800]
msgid ""
"1) Ensure that people with psychosocial disabilities have access to needed "
"support systems and to safety measures and the necessities of life, and are "
"not restricted any more than the general population."
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[802]
msgid ""
"2) Until such time as persons with psychosocial disabilities are not held in "
"institutions, governments must develop emergency plans to ensure the safety "
"of such persons during situations of armed conflict, humanitarian "
"emergencies and natural disasters. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[17]/text:list-item[0]/text:p[0]
msgid ""
"在武装冲突、人道主义紧急情况和自然灾害的情况下，要求政府尊重国际人权和人道主"
"义法律，并且采取措施确保残疾人在该种环境下的安全。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[803]
msgctxt "office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[803]"
msgid "需要做什么："
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[18]/text:list-item[0]/text:p[0]
msgid ""
"确保社会心理残疾人士能够使用需要的支持系统，以及安全措施和生命的必需品，并且"
"不能比一般大众受到更多的限制。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[822]
msgid ""
"Article 12 guarantees the right to enjoy legal capacity, including both the "
"capacity to have rights and the capacity to act (to exercise rights and "
"responsibilities and make decisions in everyday life), and requires "
"governments to provide access to support in exercising legal capacity for "
"those who may need it; any measures related to the exercise of legal "
"capacity must respect a person’s rights, will and preferences, and "
"safeguards must be established to prevent abuse."
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[823]
msgctxt "office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[823]"
msgid "What needs to be done:"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[824]
msgid ""
"Article 12 is the most innovative and far-reaching provision in the "
"Convention, and has a major significance for users and survivors of "
"psychiatry. Instead of being treated as non-persons to be acted on by "
"others, assistance will be offered in times of crisis, confusion or "
"distress, which we have the right to accept or refuse. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[825]
msgid ""
"1) Repeal guardianship and incapacity laws and provisions throughout the "
"legal system. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[826]
msgid ""
"2) Abolish the insanity defense and replace with disability-neutral "
"standards for adjudicating criminal responsibility (e.g. actual criminal "
"intent, taking account of the circumstances of the crime, motivation, etc.)."
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[827]
msgid ""
"3) Develop mechanisms to provide support in making decisions to a wide range "
"of people with disabilities with diverse needs. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[828]
msgid ""
"4) In supported decision-making, the judgment and will of the person are not "
"contested, unlike in guardianship and substituted decision-making. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[829]
msgid ""
"5) Agencies that habitually deal with acts requiring an exercise of legal "
"capacity (such as banks, notaries, judges, medical personnel) need to "
"provide some support measures as a form of reasonable accommodation. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[830]
msgid ""
"第十二条 保证享有法律能力的权利，包括拥有权利的能力和行为的能力（行使权利和承"
"担义务以及日常生活的自主做决定），并且要求政府在那些可能需要协助的人行使法律"
"能力时向他们提供便利；任何与行使法律能力相关的措施必须尊重本人的权利、意愿和"
"偏好，必须建立防护措施防止滥用。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[831]
msgid ""
"第12条是公约中最具创新性和深远意义的条款，并且对于精神病学使用者和幸存者有重"
"大意义。不是被当作其他人施加影响的卑微的人对待，而是在在危机、混乱或悲痛时刻"
"提供援助，我们对这种援助有接受或拒绝的权利。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[832]
msgctxt "office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[832]"
msgid "需要做什么："
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[19]/text:list-item[0]/text:p[0]
msgid "在整个司法系统废除监护人制度和无行为能力法律和条款。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[19]/text:list-item[1]/text:p[0]
msgid ""
"废除精神病防御和以残疾中立标准代替来判决刑事责任（例如：实际犯罪意图，考虑犯"
"罪的环境，动机等等）。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[19]/text:list-item[2]/text:p[0]
msgid ""
"在做决定中发展机制以提供协助，以达到满足有多元化需求的残疾人的广泛程度。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[19]/text:list-item[3]/text:p[0]
msgid ""
"在“支持性自主决策”中，残疾人的判断和意愿没有争议，不像在监护人制度和替代性决"
"策一样。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[19]/text:list-item[4]/text:p[0]
msgid ""
"惯常地应付需要行使法律能力的行动的机构（譬如银行、公证员、法官、医疗人员）需"
"要提供一些协助措施，以作为一种合理的便利。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[833]
msgid ""
"Article 13 guarantees access to justice for persons with disabilities, "
"including through accommodations to facilitate acting as a witness or party "
"in court proceedings and investigations, and requires training for police "
"and others involved in the administration of justice."
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[835]
msgctxt "office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[835]"
msgid "What needs to be done:"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[837]
msgid ""
"1) Provide accommodation to people with psychosocial disabilities in "
"investigations and court proceedings. Such accommodations may include access "
"to support networks, avoidance of emotional provocation, and acceptance of "
"non-conventional types of communication. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[839]
msgid ""
"2) Repeal laws whereby persons with psychosocial disabilities are "
"disqualified from being complainants or witnesses. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[841]
msgid ""
"3) Abolish provisions whereby the trials of persons with psychosocial "
"disabilities are postponed indefinitely and replace them with provisions "
"that protect the due process rights of persons with psychosocial "
"disabilities."
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[20]/text:list-item[0]/text:p[0]
msgid ""
"保证残疾人获得司法保护，包括通过便利去促使他在法律诉讼程序和调查中作为一个证"
"人或参与方，并且要求对警察和其他相关司法领域工作人员进行培训。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[845]
msgctxt "office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[845]"
msgid "需要做什么："
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[847]
msgid "2）废除使社会心理残疾人士失去成为原告和证人资格的法律。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[848]
msgid ""
"3）废除对社会心理残疾人士无限期的延长审判的法律条款，和用保护社会心理残疾人士"
"的法定诉讼程序权利来代替它们。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[870]
msgid ""
"Article 14 guarantees liberty and security of the person on an equal basis "
"with others, ensuring that disability cannot justify a deprivation of "
"liberty, and that people with disabilities deprived of liberty are entitled "
"to human rights guarantees on an equal basis with others and to reasonable "
"accommodation."
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[872]
msgctxt "office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[872]"
msgid "What needs to be done:"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[874]
msgid ""
"1) Repeal any laws that use disability as a factor to justify a deprivation "
"of liberty (e.g. mental health commitment laws). "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[876]
msgid ""
"2) Release all individuals currently deprived of liberty in psychiatric "
"settings or based on psychosocial disability."
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[878]
msgid ""
"3) Ensure equal access for people with psychosocial disabilities to "
"procedures to determine guilt or innocence of crimes, including the "
"presumption of innocence and due process. (See also “What needs to be done” "
"under Article 13, subsection 3.)"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[880]
msgid ""
"4) Provide reasonable accommodation in law enforcement procedures, court "
"proceedings and penal system. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[882]
msgid ""
"第14条 保证残疾人在与其他人平等基础上的自由和人身安全，确保不得以残疾作为剥夺"
"自由的理由，以及被剥夺自由的残疾人，在与其他人平等的基础上，有权获得人权的保"
"障的权利，和获得合理便利的待遇。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[885]
msgctxt "office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[885]"
msgid "需要做什么："
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[21]/text:list-item[0]/text:p[0]
msgid "废除任何以残疾为剥夺自由的因素的法律（例如：精神卫生收治法律）。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[21]/text:list-item[1]/text:p[0]
msgid "释放现时在精神病科环境的、或者基于社会心理残疾的被剥夺自由的所有个人。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[21]/text:list-item[2]/text:p[0]
msgid ""
"确保社会心理残疾人士拥有平等获得进入决定其是有罪还是无罪的法定程序，包括无罪"
"推定和法定诉讼程序。（同见第十三条下“需要做什么”，第三节）"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[21]/text:list-item[3]/text:p[0]
msgid "在执法程序、法律诉讼程序和刑法系统中提供合理便利。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[902]
msgid ""
"Article 15 prohibits torture and cruel, inhuman or degrading treatment or "
"punishment, including medical experimentation without consent, on people "
"with disabilities. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[903]
msgctxt "office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[903]"
msgid "What needs to be done:"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[905]
msgid ""
"Freedom from torture and cruel, inhuman or degrading treatment or punishment "
"is one of the most well established principles of international human rights "
"law. Medical experimentation without consent was first recognized as a form "
"of torture or cruel, inhuman or degrading treatment or punishment in the "
"International Covenant on Civil and Political Rights, Article 7. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[907]
msgid ""
"1) Psychiatric drugs and other invasive methods such as electroshock are "
"inherently experimental and endanger the mental and physical capacities, "
"autonomy and personality of an individual. Use of such methods without free "
"and informed consent constitutes torture or cruel, inhuman or degrading "
"treatment or punishment. The practice of forced, coerced or deceptive "
"psychiatric interventions must be stopped immediately and criminally "
"sanctioned. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[909]
msgid ""
"2) Ensure that psychiatric interventions are not used for purposes of "
"interrogation, coercion or intimidation, punishment, preventive measures, "
"for any reason based on discrimination of any kind (these are the purposes "
"of torture as defined in the UN Convention Against Torture, Article 1), or "
"for any purposes relating to the convenience of third parties. Such use must "
"be prohibited whether in psychiatric settings, prisons, residential "
"services, facilities for children or older persons, or in any other setting."
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[22]/text:list-item[0]/text:p[0]
msgid ""
"禁止对残疾人实施酷刑和残忍、不人道或有辱人格的待遇和惩罚，包括对其不同意的医"
"学试验"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[913]
msgctxt "office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[913]"
msgid "需要做什么："
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[914]
msgid ""
"免于酷刑、残忍、不人道或有辱人格的待遇或惩罚，是国际人权法中一个最得到确认的"
"原则。未经本人同意的医疗试验在《国际公民和政治权利公约》第七条中首先被视为一"
"种形式的酷刑、残忍、不人道的或有辱人格的待遇或惩罚。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[23]/text:list-item[0]/text:p[0]
msgid ""
"精神病药物和其他像电击那样的侵害性的方法是固有的试验性的，并且使个人的精神和"
"身体能力、自主权和个性受到危险。没有自由和知情同意而使用像这样的方法构成酷"
"刑、残忍 、不人道的和有辱人格的待遇或惩罚。强制性、威胁性或者欺骗性的精神病学"
"干预必须马上停止和受到刑罚制裁。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[23]/text:list-item[1]/text:p[0]
msgid ""
"确保精神病学干预在任何理由下，基于任何种类的歧视，或因为任何与第三方利益相关"
"的目的，不被用于审问、威胁或者恐吓、惩罚、预防措施的目的（基于这些目的酷刑是"
"在《联合国反酷刑公约》第一条里面定义的）。像这样的使用必须被禁止，无论是精神"
"病科环境、监狱、住宅服务、儿童或老人设施，或在任何环境。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[925]
msgid ""
"3) Some psychiatric methods may be inherently inhuman and degrading, and "
"should be banned. For example, direct electroshock makes the person "
"experience the full force of the convulsion without anesthesia, in addition "
"to the brain-damaging effects of the shock itself, and it should be "
"considered a form of torture or cruel, inhuman or degrading treatment, "
"regardless of whether consent was sought or obtained. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[927]
msgid ""
"Please note that Article 25 requires that health care be provided on the "
"basis of free and informed consent. This may be a more direct basis for "
"stopping forced, coercive and deceptive psychiatric interventions, but "
"advocates should be aware that the freedom from torture and cruel, inhuman "
"or degrading treatment or punishment is relevant and applicable."
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[929]
msgid ""
"Article 16 requires prevention of exploitation, violence and abuse, "
"including monitoring of programs designed to serve people with disabilities, "
"prosecution of violations where warranted, and measures to promote recovery "
"and reintegration of victims."
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[931]
msgctxt "office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[931]"
msgid "What needs to be done:"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[933]
msgid ""
"1) Prevent all forms of exploitation, violence and abuse in family settings, "
"communities and service provider facilities. This includes sexual abuse and "
"violence, economic exploitation and all other forms. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[24]/text:list-item[0]/text:p[0]
msgid ""
"Psychiatric interventions such as administration of drugs, electroshock or "
"psychosurgery, done against the person’s will or without free and informed "
"consent are forms of exploitation, violence and abuse that must be addressed "
"by preventive measures, monitoring, prosecution and services to victims, as "
"required by this Article."
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[936]
msgid ""
"3)一些精神病学方法可能是固有的不人道的和有辱人格的，应该被禁用。例如：直接电"
"击使人受到脑损伤的影响之外，还在没有麻醉的情况下经历抽搐的充分的力量，并且它"
"应该被认作是一种形式的酷刑、残忍、不人道、有辱人格的待遇，无论本人是否要求或"
"得到同意。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[938]
msgid ""
"请注意第二十五条，要求必须基于自由和知情同意权提供卫生保健。这也许是一个更加"
"直接的停止强制性、威胁性的和欺骗的精神病学干预的基础，但是倡导者应该意识到免"
"于酷刑、残忍、不人道、有辱人格的待遇或惩罚是相关联的和可应用的。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[25]/text:list-item[0]/text:p[0]
msgid ""
"要求防止剥削、暴力和凌虐，包括设计用于服务残疾人的方案的监督，被保证的对侵犯"
"的检举，和促进恢复和被害人的康复。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[941]
msgctxt "office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[941]"
msgid "需要做什么："
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[26]/text:list-item[0]/text:p[0]
msgid ""
"在家庭环境、社区和服务提供者的设施中，防止所有形式的剥削、暴力和凌虐。这包括"
"性虐待和暴力、经济剥削和其他各种形式。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[26]/text:list-item[1]/text:p[0]
msgid ""
"像药物施行、电击或者精神外科手术这样的违背他人意愿或没有自由和知情同意的精神"
"病学干预，是必须被防范措施、监管、检举和对被害人的服务所设法解决的剥削、暴力"
"和凌虐的形式，像本条款要求的一样。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[948]
msgid ""
"3) Survivors of exploitation, violence and abuse should have access to "
"social support and services of their choice, which should not be conditioned "
"on acceptance of a psychiatric diagnosis. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[950]
msgid ""
"4) Support should be provided to withdraw safely from psychiatric drugs. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[27]/text:list-item[0]/text:p[0]
msgid ""
"剥削、暴力和凌虐的幸存者应该获得社会支持和他们选择的服务，该支持和服务在接受"
"精神病科诊断时不应该有条件限制。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[28]/text:list-item[0]/text:p[0]
msgid "应该对安全停止精神科用药提供支持。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[956]
msgid ""
"Article 17 guarantees to people with disabilities the right to respect for "
"physical and mental integrity on an equal basis with others. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[957]
msgctxt "office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[957]"
msgid "What needs to be done:"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[959]
msgid ""
"1) The right to respect for integrity on an equal basis is violated by "
"violent or degrading practices done to people with disabilities. This right "
"can be broader than the right to be free from torture and cruel, inhuman or "
"degrading treatment or punishment, and may also be seen as its more positive "
"expression. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[961]
msgid ""
"2) The right to integrity can be used to reject the administration of "
"psychosurgery, electroshock and neuroleptic drugs on the grounds that these "
"procedures and drugs have a harmful effect on healthy organs and human "
"autonomy and creativity. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[29]/text:list-item[0]/text:p[0]
msgid "保证残疾人有权利获得在与他人平等基础上的身心完整性的尊重"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[966]
msgctxt "office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[966]"
msgid "需要做什么："
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[30]/text:list-item[0]/text:p[0]
msgid ""
"当残疾人受到暴力的或者有辱人格的做法对待时，在平等基础上的对完整性的尊重的权"
"利受到侵害。这种权利可以比免于酷刑、残忍、不人道或者有辱人格的待遇或惩罚的权"
"利更加广泛，并且可以被视为它更积极的表述。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[30]/text:list-item[1]/text:p[0]
msgid ""
"完整性的权利可以因为这些程序和药物对于健康器官和人类自主权和创造力造成伤害，"
"被用于拒绝精神外科手术、电击和的抗精神病药物的施行。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[980]
msgid ""
"Article 18 guarantees liberty of movement and freedom to choose one’s own "
"residence, the right to a nationality and the right to use processes such as "
"immigration proceedings. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[981]
msgctxt "office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[981]"
msgid "What needs to be done:"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[983]
msgid ""
"Laws and policies regarding international travel, immigration and "
"naturalization, should treat people with disabilities on an equal basis with "
"others, including reasonable accommodation. No one should be rejected from "
"entering a country based on past or present psychosocial disability."
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[31]/text:list-item[0]/text:p[0]
msgid ""
"保证自由迁徙和选择自己居所的自由，享有国籍的权利和使用像移民程序那样的程序。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[986]
msgctxt "office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[986]"
msgid "需要做什么："
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[988]
msgid ""
"关于国际旅行、移民和归化的法律和政策应该在与其他人平等的基础上对待残疾人，包"
"括合理便利。任何人不能基于过往和现在的社会心理残疾被拒绝进入一个国家。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[990]
msgid ""
"Article 19 guarantees the right to live in the community with choices equal "
"to those of others, including the choice of where and with whom to live, and "
"ensures access to services that support such life choices."
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[992]
msgctxt "office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[992]"
msgid "What needs to be done:"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[994]
msgid ""
"1) Free all our people from institutions. Ensure that no one is kept in an "
"institution against his or her will, and that housing and services are "
"provided in communities. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[996]
msgid ""
"2) Ensure that housing and services, including residential services, respect "
"individual autonomy. End coercive medication policies in residential and "
"outpatient services. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1000]
msgid ""
"第十九条 保证有与其他人平等地选择居住在社区的权利，包括选择住在哪里和与谁同住"
"的权利，并确保获得像这样的生活选择的支持。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1002]
msgctxt "office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1002]"
msgid "需要做什么："
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[32]/text:list-item[0]/text:p[0]
msgid ""
"把我们的人从各种机构中释放出来。确保没有违背任何人的意愿监禁他/她，并且在社区"
"提供住房和服务。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[32]/text:list-item[1]/text:p[0]
msgid ""
"确保住房和服务，包括住宅服务，尊重个人自主权。在居住和门诊服务中结束威胁性性"
"的药物政策。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1014]
msgid ""
"3) Community services must be accessible and open to people with "
"psychosocial disabilities, and be responsive to their needs."
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1016]
msgid ""
"4) Provide a wide array of services, developed in consultation with user/"
"survivor organizations, that may include peer support, crisis hostels and "
"places of safe respite, and advocacy. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1019]
msgid ""
"Article 20 requires states to ensure personal mobility of persons with "
"disabilities, with the greatest possible independence."
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[33]/text:list-item[0]/text:p[0]
msgid "对于残疾人，社区服务必须是容易得到和向他们开放的，并响应他们的需求。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[33]/text:list-item[1]/text:p[0]
msgid ""
"在与使用者/幸存者组织商议过程中发展并提供广泛的服务，包括残疾人相互支持、危机"
"宿舍和安全缓刑和辩护的处所。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1025]
msgid "第二十条 要求国家确保残疾人的个人流动拥有最大可能性的自主权。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1056]
msgid ""
"Article 21 requires states to ensure that persons with disabilities can "
"exercise the freedom of information and expression, through all forms of "
"communication of their choice. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1058]
msgctxt "office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1058]"
msgid "What needs to be done:"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1060]
msgid ""
"1) Ensure that persons with psychosocial disabilities are provided with full "
"and accurate information. A major discrimination faced by persons living "
"with psychosocial disabilities is that we are told what people think we "
"should be told and not provided with the information we have the right to "
"receive and obtain. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1062]
msgid ""
"2) Ensure that non-conventional communication by people with psychosocial "
"disabilities is accepted. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1064]
msgid ""
"第二十一条 要求国家通过所有残疾人选择的通讯形式，确保残疾人行使获得信息的表达"
"的自由。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1066]
msgctxt "office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1066]"
msgid "需要做什么："
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[34]/text:list-item[0]/text:p[0]
msgid ""
"确保向残疾人提供充分和准确的信息。一个社会心理残疾人士面临的重要歧视是：人们"
"以他们认为我们应该被告知的信息告知我们，而不是向我们提供我们有权利接受和获得"
"的信息。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[34]/text:list-item[1]/text:p[0]
msgid "确保社会心理残疾人士的非传统通讯被接纳。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1097]
msgid ""
"Article 22 guarantees privacy and in particular, the privacy of personal, "
"health and rehabilitation information of persons with disabilities on an "
"equal basis with others. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1098]
msgctxt "office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1098]"
msgid "What needs to be done:"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1100]
msgid ""
"Protect persons with psychosocial disabilities from being pressured to "
"release medical records during custody litigation and other court "
"proceedings on an equal basis with others. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1102]
msgid ""
"第二十二条 保证隐私，并且特别是在与其他人平等的基础上，保护残疾人个人、健康和"
"康复信息。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1104]
msgctxt "office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1104]"
msgid "需要做什么："
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1107]
msgid ""
"保护社会心理残疾人士在与其他人平等的基础上，在羁押诉讼和其他法律诉讼程序中免"
"于受到发布其医疗记录的压力。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1140]
msgid ""
"Article 23 guarantees equality in family, parenthood, marriage and "
"relationships, and the right to retain fertility, and ensures that custody "
"of children may not be deprived based on a parent’s or child’s disability. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1141]
msgctxt "office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1141]"
msgid "What needs to be done:"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1143]
msgid ""
"1) Repeal laws that disqualify people with disabilities from marriage, "
"consensual sexual relationships, or exercising parental rights. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1145]
msgid ""
"2) End forced or coerced sterilization or abortion on people with "
"psychosocial disabilities. (See also Articles 15, 16, 17.)"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1147]
msgid ""
"3) Ensure that people do not lose the right or freedom to have sexual "
"relationships in residential programs or when using the services of in-home "
"assistants."
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1149]
msgid ""
"4) Personal assistants should be available to parents with psychosocial "
"disabilities if the parents wish to have such assistance."
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1151]
msgid ""
"5) Train judges and lawyers to ensure that decisions about custody of "
"children do not reflect prejudice about parents or children with "
"disabilities."
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1153]
msgid ""
"第二十三条 保证家庭、亲子关系、婚姻和恋爱关系的平等，和保持生育的权利，并且确"
"保不能基于家长或孩子的残疾剥夺孩子的监护。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1155]
msgctxt "office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1155]"
msgid "需要做什么："
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[35]/text:list-item[0]/text:p[0]
msgid "废除使残疾人丧失结婚、经双方同意的性关系或者行使父母权利的资格的法律。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[35]/text:list-item[1]/text:p[0]
msgid "结束对残疾人强制和威胁性的绝育和堕胎。（同见第15、16、17条）"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[35]/text:list-item[2]/text:p[0]
msgid "确保人们不丧失在住宅项目或使用家庭助手服务时发生性关系的权利和自由。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[35]/text:list-item[3]/text:p[0]
msgid "如果社会心理残疾的父母需要个人助手服务，他们应该可以获得该协助。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[35]/text:list-item[4]/text:p[0]
msgid "培训法官和律师以确保儿童的监护的决定不反应对残疾家长和孩子的歧视。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1177]
msgid ""
"Article 24 guarantees the right to an inclusive education at all levels, "
"including tertiary education and lifelong learning, and that no child shall "
"be excluded from the general education system based on disability. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1178]
msgctxt "office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1178]"
msgid "What needs to be done:"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1180]
msgid ""
"1) Ensure that teachers are able to meet the diverse learning needs of "
"students, and provide a safe and respectful academic and social environment."
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1182]
msgid ""
"2) Provide support and reasonable accommodation to students with "
"psychosocial or learning disabilities. Identify and meet needs without "
"imposing labels on children."
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1184]
msgid ""
"3) Ensure that no child is excluded from education because of psychosocial "
"disability, or coerced to use mental health services or psychiatric drugs as "
"a condition for receiving an education."
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1186]
msgid ""
"4) Provide opportunities and reasonable accommodation for adults with "
"psychosocial disabilities to complete their education and participate in "
"lifelong learning. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1190]
msgid ""
"第二十四条 保证各级水平实行包容性教育，包括高等教育和终身教育，并且儿童不能被"
"基于残疾被排除在普通教育系统之外。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1192]
msgctxt "office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1192]"
msgid "需要做什么："
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[36]/text:list-item[0]/text:p[0]
msgid ""
"确保教师能够满足学生多元化的学习需求，并且提供安全和尊敬的学术和社会环境。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[36]/text:list-item[1]/text:p[0]
msgid ""
"向有社会心理残疾或学习障碍的学生提供支持或合理便利。确认和满足他们的需求，而"
"不标签化儿童。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[36]/text:list-item[2]/text:p[0]
msgid ""
"确保儿童不因为社会心理残疾被排除在教育之外，或者被威胁使用精神卫生服务或者精"
"神病药物作为接受教育的条件。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[36]/text:list-item[3]/text:p[0]
msgid "向社会心理残疾成人提供完成教育和参加终身学习的机会和合理便利。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1212]
msgid ""
"Article 25 guarantees equality in health care and services, including the "
"requirement of free and informed consent, and access to health care and "
"services related to a disability, including early identification and "
"intervention “as appropriate”."
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1214]
msgctxt "office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1214]"
msgid "What needs to be done:"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1216]
msgid ""
"1) Ensure that the right to free and informed consent is legally recognized "
"and enforced without discrimination. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1218]
msgid ""
"2) End forced/coerced medication in emergency rooms and inpatient "
"facilities. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1220]
msgid ""
"3) Develop and promote alternatives to medical model psychiatry that are "
"adequately funded and independent of medical system. Ensure that "
"alternatives exist for people to receive support for mental and emotional "
"needs without accepting a psychiatric diagnosis. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[37]/text:list-item[0]/text:p[0]
msgid ""
"Provide accurate information to people considering the use of psychiatric "
"drugs, electroshock and psychosurgery. Such information should be developed "
"in consultation with users and survivors of psychiatry with diverse "
"perspectives, including those who had adverse and traumatic experiences with "
"the interventions in question. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1225]
msgctxt "office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1225]"
msgid "需要做什么："
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[38]/text:list-item[0]/text:p[0]
msgid "确保自由表达和知情同意的权利被法律承认和没有歧视地执行。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[38]/text:list-item[1]/text:p[0]
msgid "结束在急诊室和住院设施中的强迫性/威胁性的医药使用。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[38]/text:list-item[2]/text:p[0]
msgid ""
"发展和促进医疗模式精神病学的的替代方案，这些方案受到充分资助和独立于医疗系"
"统。确保这些替代方案为不接受精神科诊断的、有精神和情绪的需求的人们接受支持而"
"存在。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1243]
msgid ""
"5) Ensure that physical health problems are not misidentified as "
"psychosocial disability."
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1245]
msgid ""
"6) Mental health screening is an inappropriate application of early "
"identification and intervention that results in labeling and discrimination "
"rather than meeting human needs. In particular, no one should be prescribed "
"psychiatric drugs as a preventive measure."
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1247]
msgid ""
"7) End discriminatory practices regarding health insurance and life "
"insurance."
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[39]/text:list-item[0]/text:p[0]
msgid "确保身体健康问题不被误诊为社会心理残疾。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[39]/text:list-item[1]/text:p[0]
msgid ""
"精神健康审查是一项导致标签化和歧视、而不是满足人类的需要的早期诊断和干预中的"
"不合适的应用。特别的，任何人不应该开精神病药方作为预防措施。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[39]/text:list-item[2]/text:p[0]
msgid "结束与医疗保险和人寿保险相关的歧视做法。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1285]
msgid ""
"Article 26 requires measures to enable people with disabilities to develop "
"their abilities to the fullest extent, including through peer support, "
"rehabilitation and habilitation."
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1287]
msgctxt "office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1287]"
msgid "What needs to be done:"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1289]
msgid ""
"Ensure that peer support is recognized and promoted in compliance with this "
"Article."
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1291]
msgid ""
"Article 27 guarantees non-discrimination and reasonable accommodation in the "
"right to work and requires positive measures to ensure that the open labor "
"market is inclusive to persons with disabilities and to promote "
"opportunities for employment, career advancement and self-employment/"
"entrepreneurship; slavery, servitude and forced labor are prohibited. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1292]
msgctxt "office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1292]"
msgid "What needs to be done:"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1294]
msgid ""
"1) Enact anti-discrimination laws and policies applicable to all forms and "
"sectors of employment, and ensure that people with psychosocial disabilities "
"are fully covered by these laws on an equal basis with all others."
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1296]
msgid ""
"2) Include people with psychosocial disabilities in programs to promote full "
"employment and economic empowerment. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1299]
msgid ""
"第二十六条 要求采取措施使得残疾人最大限度地发展他们的能力，包括通过残疾人相互"
"支持，恢复和康复。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1301]
msgctxt "office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1301]"
msgid "需要做什么："
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1302]
msgid "确保残疾人相互支持如本条款所述被承认和促进。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1304]
msgid ""
"第二十七条 保证工作的权利不受歧视和提供合理便利，并要求采取积极措施确保残疾人"
"包含在开放性劳动市场内，并促进就业、职业提升和自营就业/创业经营的机会；禁止奴"
"隶制度、奴役和强迫性劳动。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1306]
msgctxt "office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1306]"
msgid "需要做什么："
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[40]/text:list-item[0]/text:p[0]
msgid ""
"制定可应用于就业的所有形式和领域的反歧视法律和政策，并确保社会心理残疾人士在"
"与其他所有人平等基础上的充分受到这些法律和政策的保护。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[40]/text:list-item[1]/text:p[0]
msgid "把社会心理残疾人士包含进促进就业和经济赋权的项目中。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1320]
msgid ""
"3) Promote a wide range of employment opportunities and career paths without "
"discrimination based on disability."
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1322]
msgid ""
"4) Employ people with disabilities in public sector jobs for which they are "
"qualified."
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1325]
msgid ""
"5) Require reasonable accommodation in all aspects of employment and "
"qualifications for employment."
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1327]
msgid ""
"6) Promote self-employment, entrepreneurship, job sharing, higher education "
"to prepare for career of the person’s choice. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1329]
msgid ""
"7) End the exceptions to national labor laws given to sheltered workshops or "
"nonprofit organizations employing persons with disabilities. Such exceptions "
"(for example, allowing lower wages to be paid in these settings) do not help "
"people with disabilities but perpetuate exploitation (contrary to Article "
"16) and constitute discrimination. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1331]
msgid ""
"8) Employment for people with disabilities should be treated as employment "
"and not as therapy or charity. Alternative employment and social enterprises "
"are worthwhile if they pay a living wage and comply with other general "
"requirements to preserve workers’ rights and dignity. “Sheltered workshops” "
"that discriminate against persons with disabilities with respect to pay can "
"no longer operate on that basis. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[41]/text:list-item[0]/text:p[0]
msgid "在不基于残疾的歧视下，促进广泛的就业机会和职业发展路径。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[41]/text:list-item[1]/text:p[0]
msgid "在公共部门雇佣残疾人做他们能胜任的工作。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[41]/text:list-item[2]/text:p[0]
msgid "要求向就业的各个方面和就业资格提供合理便利。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[41]/text:list-item[3]/text:p[0]
msgid ""
"促进自营就业、创业经营、分享工作、和为基于个人选择的职业做准备的高等教育。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[41]/text:list-item[4]/text:p[0]
msgid ""
"结束国家劳动法给予雇佣残疾人的庇护工场或非牟利组织的例外。像这样的例外（例"
"如，在这些环境中容许支付更低的工资）不但没有帮助残疾人，而且还使剥削（与第十"
"六条相反）长期保持下去和构成歧视。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[41]/text:list-item[5]/text:p[0]
msgid ""
"残疾人就业应被视为工作，而不是治疗或慈善。如果其他就业和社会企业支付最低生活"
"工资和遵从其他保护工人的权利和尊严的一般要求，也是有价值的。至于谈到歧视残疾"
"人的“庇护工场”支付的工资，基于该原则不应该再运作下去。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1349]
msgid ""
"Article 28 guarantees an adequate standard of living and access to social "
"protection and poverty reduction programs, and to assistance with disability-"
"related expenses, including respite care, for people with disabilities "
"living in situations of poverty. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1350]
msgctxt "office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1350]"
msgid "What needs to be done:"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1352]
msgid ""
"1) Take all necessary measures to realize an adequate standard of living for "
"people with psychosocial disabilities, including adequate food, water, "
"clothes and housing. No one should be forced to enter an institution for "
"lack of the necessities of life."
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1354]
msgid ""
"2) Ensure that development and poverty reduction programs include, and are "
"responsive to, people with psychosocial disabilities. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1357]
msgid ""
"第二十八条 对生活在贫穷状态下的残疾人，保证获得适足的生活水平和利用社会保护项"
"目和减贫项目，并且与残疾相关的费用支出的援助，包括临时看护。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1359]
msgctxt "office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1359]"
msgid "需要做什么："
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[42]/text:list-item[0]/text:p[0]
msgid ""
"采取一切必要的措施以使社会心理残疾人士实现适足生活水平，包括适足的食物、供"
"水、衣服和住房。不应该强迫任何人因为缺乏生活必需品进入机构。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[42]/text:list-item[1]/text:p[0]
msgid "确保发展项目和减贫项目包括社会心理残疾人士，并且响应他们的需求。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1389]
msgid ""
"Article 29 guarantees equality in political and public participation, "
"including the right and opportunity of people with disabilities to vote and "
"be elected, and obligates governments to promote the participation of people "
"with disabilities in the conduct of public affairs, including through "
"disabled people’s organizations. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1390]
msgctxt "office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1390]"
msgid "What needs to be done:"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1392]
msgid ""
"1) Ensure that no one is disqualified from voting on the basis of "
"psychosocial disability. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1394]
msgid "2) Ensure that people who are in institutions have the right to vote. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1396]
msgid ""
"3) Recognize and support organizations of users and survivors of psychiatry "
"on the national, regional, international and local levels. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1399]
msgid ""
"第二十九条 保证参与政治和公共活动的平等，包括残疾人投票和被选举的权利和机会，"
"和使政府承担促进残疾人参与处理公共事务的责任，包括通过残疾人组织。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1401]
msgctxt "office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1401]"
msgid "需要做什么："
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[43]/text:list-item[0]/text:p[0]
msgid "确保任何人不能基于社会心理残疾被取消投票的资格。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[43]/text:list-item[1]/text:p[0]
msgid "确保在机构中的人拥有投票的权利。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[43]/text:list-item[2]/text:p[0]
msgid ""
"在国家、地区、国际和本地等各层面承认和支持精神病学的使用者和幸存者组织。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1430]
msgid ""
"Article 30 guarantees, among other things, the right to participate in "
"cultural activities and to utilize one’s creative and intellectual "
"potential, and the right of people with disabilities to respect and support "
"for their cultural identities."
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1432]
msgctxt "office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1432]"
msgid "What needs to be done:"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1434]
msgid ""
"1) Provide opportunities for people with psychosocial disabilities to "
"develop themselves and contribute to art, science and other cultural work."
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1436]
msgid ""
"2) Ensure that cultural productions and sports and recreation opportunities "
"do not discriminate against the participation of people with psychosocial "
"disabilities as participants or spectators. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1438]
msgid ""
"3) Protect the rights of people with psychosocial disabilities to practice "
"their own indigenous, traditional and/or minority cultures, and to develop "
"programs and services that are culturally competent and acceptable. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1440]
msgid ""
"第三十条 除其他事项外，保证参加文化活动和利用个人创造和智力潜力的权利，而且尊"
"重和支持残疾人的文化身份的权利。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1442]
msgctxt "office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1442]"
msgid "需要做什么："
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[44]/text:list-item[0]/text:p[0]
msgid ""
"向社会心理残疾人士提供发展自我和为艺术、科学和其他文化工作做贡献的机会。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[44]/text:list-item[1]/text:p[0]
msgid ""
"确保文化产品、运动和娱乐机会不会歧视作为参与者或者观众的社会心理残疾人士的参"
"与。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[44]/text:list-item[2]/text:p[0]
msgid ""
"保护社会心理残疾人士实践他们自己天生的、传统的和/或少数群体文化的权利，并且发"
"展文化方面有竞争力和可接受的项目和服务。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1466]
msgid ""
"Article 31 requires governments to collect information (including "
"statistical and research data), in a manner that complies with "
"confidentiality safeguards and international norms on the collection and use "
"of statistics, to enable them to formulate policies to give effect to the "
"Convention."
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1468]
msgctxt "office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1468]"
msgid "What needs to be done:"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1470]
msgid ""
"Ensure that user/survivor organizations have input into the decision of what "
"type of information is collected, how it is used, and whether or not it is "
"disaggregated based on the type of disability (e.g. whether statistics about "
"employment rates of people with disabilities are further broken down to show "
"people with psychosocial disabilities compared with people with intellectual "
"disabilities, blind, deaf and deafblind people, people with physical "
"disabilities, etc.). "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1472]
msgid ""
"Article 32 requires governments to promote and engage in international "
"cooperation to realize the objectives of the Convention, including "
"activities done in partnership with organizations of people with "
"disabilities, by measures such as including people with disabilities in "
"international development programs, facilitating capacity-building, "
"cooperation in research, and technical and economic assistance. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[45]/text:list-item[0]/text:p[0]
msgid ""
"要求政府在遵行保密防护措施和关于收集和使用统计数据的国际规范下，收集信息（包"
"括统计和研究数据），使他们能够制定政策以落实公约。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1475]
msgctxt "office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1475]"
msgid "需要做什么："
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1477]
msgid ""
"确保使用者/幸存者组织投入到下列事项的决定中：收集了什么信息、信息如何使用、和"
"它是否基于残疾的类型被分解（例如：关于残疾人就业率的统计数据是否被进一步划"
"分，去通过与智力残疾人士、盲人、聋人和盲聋人、身体残疾人士等等比较来说明社会"
"心理残疾人的情况）"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1479]
msgid ""
"第32条 要求政府促进和参加国际合作来实现公约的目标，包括与残疾人组织进行合作完"
"成的活动，这是通过采取像这样的把残疾人包括在国际发展项目中、促进能力建设、研"
"究合作以及技术和经济援助之中的措施来实现。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1499]
msgctxt "office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1499]"
msgid "What needs to be done:"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1501]
msgid ""
"1) Ensure that international development programs comply with the letter and "
"spirit of the Convention, i.e. that they support activities to give effect "
"to the human rights of people with disabilities as set out in the "
"Convention, and that they do not support activities that violate the "
"Convention or discriminate against people with disabilities."
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1503]
msgid ""
"2) Support capacity-building of user/survivor organizations according to the "
"needs identified by those organizations. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1505]
msgid ""
"3) Ensure that user/survivor organizations at the international, regional, "
"national and local levels have a consultative role in international "
"cooperation activities, and can contribute as partners. This may require "
"financial support and capacity building. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1508]
msgctxt "office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1508]"
msgid "需要做什么："
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[46]/text:list-item[0]/text:p[0]
msgid ""
"确保国际发展项目遵从公约的字面意义和精神，例如，他们支持落实公约阐述的残疾人"
"的人权的活动，和他们不支持违反公约或歧视残疾人的活动。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[46]/text:list-item[1]/text:p[0]
msgid "根据由使用者/幸存者组织确认的需求，支持他们的能力建设。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[46]/text:list-item[2]/text:p[0]
msgid ""
"确保使用者/幸存者组织在国际、地区、国家和本地层面都在国际合作活动中拥有协商的"
"角色，并且能够作为伙伴作出贡献。这可能要求财务支援和能力建设。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1536]
msgid ""
"Article 33 requires governments to set up separate mechanisms for "
"implementation of the Convention and for monitoring of the convention, at a "
"national level. The monitoring function can be done by a national human "
"rights institution or a separate mechanism that meets the requirements for "
"national human rights institutions, in particular independence from the "
"political authorities. Organizations of people with disabilities are to be "
"involved and participate fully in the monitoring process. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1537]
msgctxt "office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1537]"
msgid "What needs to be done:"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1539]
msgid ""
"1) The national focal point for implementation must have a mechanism to "
"consult closely with user/survivor organizations. Implementation of Article "
"33 can also draw on Rule 17 of the Standard Rules on the Equalization of "
"Opportunities for Persons with Disabilities, which required governments to "
"set up a coordinating mechanism on disability issues that includes "
"organizations of people with disabilities. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1541]
msgid ""
"2) National monitoring is a new feature for a human rights treaty, but many "
"countries have national human rights institutions with varying powers. The "
"establishment of a monitoring mechanism, or assigning the monitoring "
"function to an existing human rights institution, must be done in "
"consultation with user/survivor organizations, and provide for an ongoing "
"role of user/survivor organizations in contributing to its work. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1543]
msgid ""
"3) The monitoring mechanism should include qualified users and survivors of "
"psychiatry as members and/or employees."
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[47]/text:list-item[0]/text:p[0]
msgid ""
"要求政府在国家的层面，为实施公约和监管公约，设立独立机制。监督功能可以由一个"
"国家人权机构或者一个满足国家人权机构要求的独立机制来完成，特别是独立于政治机"
"关。残疾人组织应当获邀并充分参与监测进程。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1546]
msgctxt "office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1546]"
msgid "需要做什么："
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[48]/text:list-item[1]/text:p[0]
msgid ""
"国家对人权条约的监督是一项新特点，但是许多国家拥有各种各样权利的国家人权机"
"构。一个监督机制的建立，或者指定一个现存的人权机构执行监督功能，必须通过与使"
"用者/幸存者组织进行商议来完成 ，并且为使用者/幸存者组织提供一个持续的角色以促"
"使他们有助于该项工作。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[48]/text:list-item[2]/text:p[0]
msgid "监督机制应当包括有资格的精神病学的使用者和幸存者作为成员和/或雇员。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1561]
msgid ""
"Articles 34 through 39 and the Optional Protocol to the Convention deal with "
"the creation and responsibilities of an international committee of experts "
"to monitor the Convention. Governments are encouraged to nominate experts "
"with disabilities to serve on this committee. Governments must report to the "
"committee and consult organizations of people with disabilities in preparing "
"these reports; organizations of people with disabilities can also "
"communicate with the committee directly to inform them about the situation "
"in their country. People with disabilities whose human rights have been "
"violated can make a complaint to the committee if their government has "
"ratified the optional protocol. The committee also has the power to "
"investigate “grave and systematic” human rights violations, including "
"through country visits, if a country has ratified the optional protocol. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1562]
msgctxt "office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1562]"
msgid "What needs to be done:"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1564]
msgid ""
"1) Establish an open and transparent process for nominating candidates for "
"the monitoring committee, seeking qualified people with disabilities and "
"candidates supported by disabled people’s organizations."
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1566]
msgid ""
"2) Comply with reporting requirements and invite the contribution of user/"
"survivor organizations to national reports."
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1568]
msgid ""
"3) Support the monitoring committee in seeking and receiving communications "
"from people with disabilities and disabled people’s organizations. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1570]
msgid ""
"4) Cooperate with the committee and with disabled people’s organizations in "
"improving compliance with the Convention. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[49]/text:list-item[0]/text:p[0]
msgid ""
"至第39条 公约的可选协议书应付监督公约的国际专家委员会的创建和责任。政府被鼓励"
"提名残疾人专家在委员会服务。政府必须向委员会报告和在准备这些报告时与残疾人组"
"织商议，残疾人组织也可以直接与委员会沟通来告知委员会关于他们国家的情况。如果"
"政府批准可选协议书，人权受到侵犯的残疾人可以向委员会投诉。如果国家批准可选协"
"议书，委员会也有调查“严重的和有系统的”侵犯人权的权利，包括通过对国家的访问，"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1573]
msgctxt "office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1573]"
msgid "需要做什么："
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1574]
msgid ""
"1）为向监察委员会提名候选人建立一个开放和透明的程序，寻找合资格的残疾人和受残"
"疾人组织支持的候选人。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1575]
msgid "2）遵从报告要求，并邀请使用者/幸存者组织对国家报告作出贡献。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1576]
msgid "3）在寻求和接收来自残疾人和残疾人组织的沟通时支持监察委员会。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1577]
msgid "4）在改进遵从公约时与委员会和残疾人组织合作。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1590]
msgid ""
"Article 40 provides for the conference of states parties to consider matters "
"related to implementation of the Convention. This is a new feature for a "
"human rights Convention and will facilitate regular exchange of information "
"and capacity building by governments and civil society, including "
"organizations of people with disabilities."
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1592]
msgctxt "office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1592]"
msgid "What needs to be done:"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1594]
msgid ""
"1) Support the active participation of disabled people’s organizations in "
"the Conference of States Parties when it considers matters related to "
"implementation of the Convention, for example to contribute to setting an "
"agenda, making presentations, and participating in panels and discussions. "
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1596]
msgid ""
"2) Contribute financial support for people with disabilities from the Global "
"South to attend these meetings."
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[50]/text:list-item[0]/text:p[0]
msgid ""
"为缔约国会议做准备，使其考虑与实行公约相关的事情。这是人权公约的一个新特点，"
"并且会促进政府和民间社会之间的定期信息交流和能力建立，民间社会包括残疾人组"
"织。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1600]
msgctxt "office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:p[1600]"
msgid "需要做什么："
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[51]/text:list-item[0]/text:p[0]
msgid ""
"当缔约国会议考虑与实行公约相关的事情时，支持残疾人组织积极参与到会议中，例"
"如，做贡献于设立议事日程，提交演示，和参加专家小组和讨论。"
msgstr ""

#: office:document-content[0]/office:body[0]/office:text[0]/text:list[51]/text:list-item[1]/text:p[0]
msgid "从圣公会环南联盟向残疾人提供财务支持以参加这些会议。"
msgstr ""

